From f40e7a67742c3ed4209306aee1056d2869978bfb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: chasey-dev <ellenyoung0912@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 25 Nov 2025 00:11:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 37/64] iwinfo: fix kernel warning when accessing NAND
 partitions The current implementation constructs a "/dev/mtdblockX" path to
 read the 'Factory' partition for hardware ID detection.

On targets using SPI-NAND, accessing a NAND partition via the block emulation layer (mtdblock) triggers repetitive kernel warnings:
```log
mtdblock: MTD device 'Factory' is NAND, please consider using UBI block devices instead.
```
This results in significant log spam when applications like LuCI frequently query iwinfo.

This commit switches the access method from the block device ("/dev/mtdblockX") to the character device ("/dev/mtdX").

The character device interface:
1. Eliminates the kernel warning on NAND devices.
2. Supports the required read() operations correctly.
3. Does not handle bad block mapping itself (depends on the underlying driver), ensuring data validity without the overhead or restrictions of the mtdblock layer.

Signed-off-by: chasey-dev <ellenyoung0912@gmail.com>
---
 .../iwinfo/patches/0005-use-char-device-to-read.patch | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 package/network/utils/iwinfo/patches/0005-use-char-device-to-read.patch

diff --git a/package/network/utils/iwinfo/patches/0005-use-char-device-to-read.patch b/package/network/utils/iwinfo/patches/0005-use-char-device-to-read.patch
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..78f87aebc5
--- /dev/null
+++ b/package/network/utils/iwinfo/patches/0005-use-char-device-to-read.patch
@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@
+--- a/iwinfo_utils.c
++++ b/iwinfo_utils.c
+@@ -367,7 +367,7 @@ int iwinfo_hardware_id_from_mtd(struct i
+ 	if (off < 0)
+ 		return -1;
+ 
+-	snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "/dev/mtdblock%d", off);
++	snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "/dev/mtd%d", off);
+ 
+ 	if ((fd = open(buf, O_RDONLY)) < 0)
+ 		return -1;
